The paper deals with the problem of inserting multiple edges into a planar graph while minimizing the number of pairwise edge crossings. This problem is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) as it involves graph drawing and crossing minimization. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper presents algorithms with approximation guarantees, which indicates that it may also belong to the category of theoretical computer science (cs.GT) or computational complexity (cs.CC).
